There&#x27;s a bit of code to try and stop path traversal, but it doesn&#x27;t account for passing d=.. as a url param.<p>A shortened test case using the same code as the app to try and thwart traversal:<p><pre><code>  <?php
    $_GET[&#x27;d&#x27;]=&#x27;..&#x27;;
    $photo_dir=&#x27;photos/&#x27;;
    $sub_photo_dir = basename($_GET[&#x27;d&#x27;]).&#x27;/&#x27;;
    $photo_dir = str_replace(&quot;//&quot;,
      &quot;/&quot;,$photo_dir.$sub_photo_dir);
    print &quot;photo_dir: [$photo_dir]&quot;;
  ?>
</code></pre>
That would allow you to upload a file one directory above the intended $photo_dir.
